headline: Will PayPal Bank Push Transform PayPal Holdings' (PYPL) Narrative Into Full‑Scale Digital Banking?
summary: Earlier in December, PayPal applied to establish PayPal Bank, a Utah-chartered industrial loan company that would offer FDIC-insured savings accounts, expand small‑business lending, and reduce its reliance on partner banks by holding deposits and accessing payment networks directly. This push into banking marks a material shift in PayPal’s business model, moving it closer to full‑service financial intermediation and potentially reshaping how it funds and delivers its lending, payments, and...
